content:
Make Your Landing Pages More Accessible and Secure

Improve the security of landing pages that have forms by adding Google reCAPTCHA, and make them easier to find with search engine optimization (SEO) properties. Before publishing, preview a landing page as a guest or authenticated user.

Boost Your Landing Page in Search Engine Results

Add it to a sitemap to surface your landing page to search engine results. Add SEO properties like a page description and the <link>, <meta>, and <script> head tags to your landing page. The public page title SEO property is now required.

Safeguard Landing Pages with Forms Using reCAPTCHA

Protect forms on marketing landing pages from bots, fraudulent activities, spam, and abuse with Google reCAPTCHA.

Preview Landing Pages as a Guest or Authenticated User

Preview a landing page as a guest user to see how it looks for a broad audience. Preview it as an authenticated user to see how it looks to a customer who's logged in.

See Flow Details When You Publish a Landing Page

Review the details of the flow associated with a form when publishing a landing page.

Activate the URL Alias When You Publish a Landing Page

The inactive or draft URL alias automatically activates after a landing page successfully publishes, making your public URL live.
title: Improving Landing Pages with Google reCAPTCHA and SEO
